In his remarks at the United Nations General Assembly, President Trump addressed various issues including the COVID-19 pandemic, China's responsibility for the virus, environmental concerns, human rights, America's military strength, and international peace agreements. He highlighted the efforts made by the United States in combating the pandemic, developing vaccines, and distributing them globally. President Trump also criticized China for its handling of the virus and its environmental practices. He emphasized the need for the United Nations to focus on real global problems such as terrorism, human trafficking, and religious persecution. The President also highlighted America's economic prosperity, military strength, and achievements in international relations, including peace agreements in the Middle East and efforts to end the war in Afghanistan. He expressed confidence in a brighter future and emphasized the importance of putting one's own country first.